I think he did not touch the ball even as Sarfraz hung onto a sharp catch, moving to his left. Chibhabha has to wait for his maiden century

commentary: Hammad Azam to Mutumbami, 1 run They go to the TV umpire. Mutumbami has lost his bat. NOT OUT is the call. On a length and outside off, Mutumbami pushes at it and gets an inner edge to short fine leg, sets off. Wahab nails a direct hit at the non-strikers' end. Top throw. Mutumbami's bat had got stuck into the turf as he tried to slide his bat in. He manages to sprint over, lands his foot down just before the bails came off

commentary: Mupariwa to Azhar Ali, OUT he has! With a short ball that's beem smashed straight to point. Good innings, set up the chase very well.
